Vegetarian Red Borscht|0
By David Tanis|0
By David Tanis|0
Yield 6 to 8 servings|0
Time 1 hour|0
EmailShare on PinterestShare on FacebookShare on Twitter|0
EmailShare on PinterestShare on FacebookShare on Twitter|0
David Malosh for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Simon Andrews.|0
David Malosh for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Simon Andrews.|0
Featured in: Sweet, Sour And Brilliantly Red.|0
More|0
Soups And Stews, Vegetables, Beet, Celery, Horseradish, Leek, Potato, Dinner, Lunch, Main Course, Fall, Winter, Vegan, Vegetarian|0
Soups And Stews, Vegetables, Beet, Celery, Horseradish, Leek, Potato, Dinner, Lunch, Main Course, Fall, Winter, Vegan, Vegetarian|0
2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil or unsalted butter|1
1 large onion, diced (about 1 1/2 cups)|1
1 cup diced celery|1
1 large leek, diced (about 1 cup)|1
Salt and pepper|1
4 garlic cloves, minced|1
1 tablespoon tomato paste|1
1 teaspoon paprika|1
teaspoon caraway seeds|1
1 bay leaf|1
1 thyme sprig|1
1 pound Yukon Gold or other starchy potatoes (about 6 potatoes), peeled and cut in 1-inch chunks|1
1 pound medium beets (about 6 beets), peeled and cut in 1-inch chunks|1
pound medium carrots (about 4 carrots), peeled and cut in 1-inch chunks|1
3 cups chopped kale|1
1 tablespoon apple-cider vinegar, or to taste|1
2 tablespoons grated fresh horseradish|1
1 tablespoon lemon juice|1
teaspoon salt|1
Pinch of granulated sugar|1
1 cup crme frache or thick sour cream|1
Dill, parsley, tarragon and chives, for garnish|1
Ingredient Substitution Guide|0
Nutritional Information|0
Note: The information shown is Edamams estimate based on available ingredients and preparation. It should not be considered a substitute for a professional nutritionists advice.|0
Powered by Edamam|0
Put olive oil in a heavy-bottomed soup pot or Dutch oven over medium-high heat.|0
Add kale and vinegar, and stir to distribute. Taste broth and adjust seasoning. Simmer until kale is done, about 8 minutes.|0
Meanwhile, make the horseradish cream: Put horseradish, lemon juice, salt and sugar in a small bowl. Let macerate 5 minutes, then stir in crme frache.|0
To serve, ladle into soup bowls, and garnish with chopped dill, parsley, tarragon and chives. Pass the horseradish cream at the table.|0
